cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.NE, cs.RO, cs.CB

The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network (CNN) that uses electroencephalography (EEG) to predict movement intent and reaction time for rehabilitation robots. This involves machine learning and human-computer interaction (HCI), which are both covered by cs.LG and cs.HC. The use of EEG also suggests a potential connection to neural engineering (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper focuses on the application of the proposed method to rehabilitation robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and possibly also computational biology (cs.CB) if the rehabilitation task involves biological systems.
